<apex:page sidebar="false" showHeader="false" title="SnapIt Metadata Xplorer Help">

	<apex:stylesheet value="{!URLFOR($Resource.SnapItMetadataXplorerResources, '/SnapItMetadataXplorerResources/css/SnapItMetadataXplorerStyle.css')}"/>

	<div class="generalBold">
	 <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
	 	<tr>
	 		<td><apex:image value="{!URLFOR($Resource.SnapItMetadataXplorerResources, '/SnapItMetadataXplorerResources/img/Help.jpg')}"/></td>
	 		<td><apex:sectionHeader id="header" title="Usage Guidelines for SnapIt Metadata Xplorer"/></td>
	 	</tr>
	 </table>
	</div>
	
	<apex:pageBlock >
		<div align="left">
			<b>Overview:</b><br><br/>
			SnapIt Metadata Xplorer allows you to view metadata details on screen. Snapshots of objects including field types, picklist details, 
			and other metadata are made available. It also allows the retreived metadata to be exported to Excel and PDF formats.
			<p>
			<p><b>Step by Step Usage Summary:</b></p>
			<ol>
				<li>Select 1, multiple or all Sobjects in the list to view their Metadata details. Use Ctrl + A to select all Sobjects 
		 			in the list or select specific Sobjects using Ctrl + Mouse Click.</li><br/>
				<li>Select the field category to view the fields for the selected Sobjects from the available options - <i>All Fields</i>, <i>Standard Fields</i>, <i>Custom Fields</i>. </li><br/>
				<ul>
					<li><b><i>All Fields:</i></b> Select this option to view all the fields that exist for the selected Sobjects.</li><br/>
					<li><b><i>Standard Fields:</i></b> Select this option to view all the Standard fields that exist for the selected Sobjects.</li><br/>
					<li><b><i>Custom Fields:</i></b> Select this option to view all the Custom fields that exist for the selected Sobjects.</li><br/>
				</ul>
				<li>Click <b>Show Metadata</b> to display the metadata details for the selected Sobjects on screen.</li><br/>
				<li>Click <b>First</b>, <b>Next</b>, <b>Prev</b>, <b>Last</b> to navigate through the batches of retreived metadata details.</li><br/>
				<li>Click <b>Export to Excel</b> to export the metadata currently displayed on screen, to an Excel spreadsheet.</li><br/>
				<li>Click <b>Export to PDF</b> to export the metadata currently displayed on screen, to a PDF.</li>
			</ol> 
		</div>
		
		<div align="left">
			<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
				<tr>
					<td><apex:image value="{!URLFOR($Resource.SnapItMetadataXplorerResources, '/SnapItMetadataXplorerResources/img/Warning.jpg')}"/></td>
					<td><b>Points to Remember !!</b></td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			
			<p>The selected Sobject list's metadata is extracted in batches, to avoid hitting the Salesforce Governor Limits.The application may take time to display 
			   the metadata details, depending upon the number of Sobjects selected.<br/> 
			Data is displayed in multiple pages with options to export to Excel or PDF. Each page needs to be exported separately.</p>
		</div>	
